&lt;h2&gt;In a nutshell&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Buyer, you own the end-to-end performance of a newly built category. You shape the assortment, define the strategy, and drive both customer value and profitability. Working closely with your team and suppliers, you turn data and insights into smart commercial decisions.&amp;nbsp;This is a role for someone who enjoys building things from the ground up. In a fast-growing, data-driven environment, you’ll set up ways of working, identify opportunities, and continuously improve the category - from supplier partnerships and pricing strategies to range quality and supply chain performance. You combine entrepreneurial thinking with hands-on execution to create real, measurable impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Tricks of the trade&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Category planning &amp;amp; analytics: &lt;/strong&gt;Build and own a comprehensive category plan from the ground up, translating data, customer insights, and market trends into clear objectives, KPIs, and actionable initiatives. Use strong analytical skills to evaluate performance, identify opportunities, and steer commercial decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Category expertise: &lt;/strong&gt;Develop deep category knowledge by combining internal data, customer insights, market trends, and supplier input.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Negotiation strategies:&lt;/strong&gt; Define and execute clear negotiation strategies to secure competitive commercial conditions with suppliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supplier negotiations&lt;/strong&gt;: Lead negotiations end-to-end with a diverse supplier base, from preparation through to signed agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial opportunities: &lt;/strong&gt;Continuously identify and prioritize commercial opportunities using a data-first approach, building solid business cases to support decisions and drive innovation and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Category improvements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design and implement improvement plans&lt;/strong&gt; to enhance range quality, performance, and customer relevance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supply chain understanding&lt;/strong&gt;: Build a strong understanding of the end-to-end supply chain and identify opportunities to improve availability, efficiency, product quality, and margins.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team collaboration: &lt;/strong&gt;Work closely with your category team and cross-functional stakeholders to define priorities, set up processes, and bring the category to the next level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Your superpowers&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MSc. degree&lt;/strong&gt; in Business Administration, (Business) Economics, or a comparable field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2+ years of experience &lt;/strong&gt;as a Buyer and/or Category Manager within a relevant non-food or consumer goods environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong entrepreneurial mindset;&lt;/strong&gt; you’re comfortable building things from scratch and making progress in an evolving setup&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience&lt;/strong&gt; (or strong ambition) in &lt;strong&gt;setting up a new category&lt;/strong&gt;, including defining ways of working, processes, and success metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong a

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In a nutshell&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Picnic, every feature, campaign, and update is designed with our customers in mind. As a &lt;strong&gt;Campaign Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, you’ll be at the heart of our customer marketing and weekly campaigns - from product launches to Christmas promotions. Your job? Telling the right story, in the right place, at the right time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll run end-to-end campaigns, set up and monitor communications, drive engagement through creative activations, and use data to boost impact. Whether it’s testing new ideas or pushing weekly sales, you’ll help grow our customer base and keep them coming back.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tricks of the trade&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Plan and execute 360 campaigns:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and manage cross-channel campaigns to create cohesive and engaging customer experiences like our Christmas campaign.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Set up and monitor communications:&lt;/strong&gt; Create and oversee creation and delivery of newsletters, push notifications, and other weekly and daily communications to keep customers informed and drive visits to our app.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Highlight features and assortment:&lt;/strong&gt; Communicate the value of Picnic’s features and product range to inspire and inform customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A/B testing:&lt;/strong&gt; Perform experiments to optimize communication strategies and improve campaign performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Boost weekly sales:&lt;/strong&gt; Set up and execute targeted sales pushes to drive extra demand and meet business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate across teams:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with analysts, creatives, and other Picnic teams to ensure campaigns deliver maximum impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your superpowers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have a Master’s degree&lt;/strong&gt; in Marketing Management, Marketing Intelligence, Business, Communication Science, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You bring &lt;strong&gt;1-2 years of experience&lt;/strong&gt; in marketing or a similar role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a &lt;strong&gt;sharp eye for detail &lt;/strong&gt;and take pride in delivering high-quality, accurate work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re great at &lt;strong&gt;multitasking &lt;/strong&gt;and keeping cool under tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re both a &lt;strong&gt;creative thinker and a data lover -&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;turning insights into action comes naturally to you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You speak and write&lt;strong&gt; fluently in both Dutch and English.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re confident working in Excel &lt;/strong&gt;and comfortable making decisions based on large datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with marketing automation tools like Selligent or Braze is a big plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Picnic perks&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🥗Fresh Lunch, coffee, and snacks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our offices are equipped with fully-fledged coffee bars and a kitchen and chefs. They prepare delicious fresh and warm lunches every day so you can keep your energy up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🚴🏼‍♂️Health insurance discount &amp;amp; bike plan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a partnership with CZ (a health insurance provider). Picnic employees get a discount on CZ insurance packages between 5% and 15%. Furthermore, through our partnership with Lease a Bike, you can rent-to-own a new (e)bike at a discounted rate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;✍🏼 Learning &amp;amp; development&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll get ample opportunity to work on yourself at Picnic. We offer personal development through Lepaya courses, Academy trainings, and more.

